channel.title: What was the point of aryan?
channel.description:
I know I'm gonna get flamed but this is just to confirm the way aryan was used,Wether its to item create or what????
What did it do?Was its purpose the same as SCAR's?Just wondering cause I am not very sure since I came in late.

item.title: What was the point of aryan?
item.dc:creator: @Exernet Exernet
item.description:
@Exernet wrote:

[quote=“nachboy, post:18, topic:7675”][quote author=shangtsung1 link=topic=10773.msg263685#msg263685 date=1158935514]
aryan was a java client
it used javascript for it’s autoing scripts
used it’s own mouse (u could play computer and auto at same time with this feature)
you could multilog (auto on 7vrel accounts at once)
it had state of the art anti randoms

*the point? it was to auto (and learn)
[/quote]

thankyou… now everyone shush-up[br][size=1]Posted at: October 27, 2006, 03:04:51 AM[/size][hr][quote author=shangtsung1 link=topic=10773.msg263685#msg263685 date=1158935514]
aryan was a java client
it used javascript for it’s autoing scripts
used it’s own mouse (u could play computer and auto at same time with this feature)
you could multilog (auto on 7vrel accounts at once)
it had state of the art anti randoms

*the point? it was to auto (and learn)
[/quote]

thankyou… now everyone shush-up[/quote]

You tell everyone to shush-up after bumping up a 1 month old thread… lol

Oh and whoever you quoted is wrong. Scripts were made in Java, not JavaScript. And it uses action-forcing, not it’s own mouse.
